libeat. The subjunctive after dum belongs to the ‘final’ class. Dum with the indicative is good Latin in the sense of ‘till,’ but it simply relates the sequence of the two facts: as, Caelum obscurum erat dum luna exorta est. Dum with the subjunctive expresses the expecta- tion or purpose, as expecto dum venias.

Hence the subjunctive is much commonet.
